               <p>482. <persName id="def1-482-18650410" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-482-18650410" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-482-18650410" type="age" value="45"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-482-18650410" type="surname" value="BROOKS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-482-18650410" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">GEORGE BROOKS</hi>
                  </persName> was <hi rend="italic">again</hi> indicted<rs id="t18650410-482-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18650410-482-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18650410-482-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="other"></interp>for unlawfully having in his custody and possession 6 pieces of leather, knowing them to be marked with the Government mark.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. POLAND</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution, and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. LILLET</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">the Defence.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-620" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-620" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-620" type="surname" value="RANDALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-620" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN RANDALL</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">gave the same evidence as in the preceding case.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-621" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-621" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-621" type="surname" value="OSBORN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-621" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN OSBORN</persName>
                  </hi>. <hi rend="italic">The evidence given by this witness was read over, and he added</hi>,—"I find the broad arrow on some of these pieces of leather."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Supposing a skin were damaged, would they sell it out of stock? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> If it was unserviceable; they take care not to buy damaged leather.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Have you ever known leather sold? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> It is said in large</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186504100190"></xptr>
               <p>quantities in the Arsenal, but not leather like this—I have not been present at any sales.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">The evidence of John Newton, James William Crouch, and John Morris, as given in the last case, was read over to them; to which they assented.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18650410-name-622" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-622" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-622" type="surname" value="M'OUBRAY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18650410-name-622" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM M'OUBRAY</persName>
                  </hi>. I am storeholder in the Royal Arsenal—I have charge of the condemned stores; I have the superintending of the sales of all of then—I have seen the leather produced here to-day; this large piece is seat-leather, to cover cloaks, and for other purposes—leather of this kind is never sold; it is new serviceable leather, unconverted—this hide is Govern<lb></lb>ment leather blacked; that is also new, serviceable leather—this is some more of the same not coloured—I have seen it all—I find the broad arrow on some of it, and the War Department mark.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> What stores pass through your hands? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Leather and blankets, chiefly the stores from foreign stations—blankets are not always torn in four before they are sold—those that I sell are chiefly horse<lb></lb>blankets, and I have sold the others as horse-blankets—if a skin of leather became damaged, it would be made convertible for the repairs of the De<lb></lb>partment work—sales take place once a quarter; up to two years back we used to have them more frequently—the last sale I had was on 12th Decem<lb></lb>ber—I have a foreman to assist me, but under my superintendence—I see everything as it is laid out.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. POLAND</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Do you find that this leather is damaged, so that it could not be use? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; it is fit for use.</p>
               <p>
